'''vsftpd''' ('''V'''ery '''S'''ecure '''FTP''' '''D'''aemon) is an FTP server for UNIX-like systems.

== Installation ==

=== USE flags ===

{{USEflag|package=net-ftp/vsftpd}}

=== Emerge ===

{{Emerge|net-ftp/vsftpd}}

== Configuration ==

==== Anonymous read access ====

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/vsftpd/vsftpd.conf|1=
listen=YES
local_enable=NO
anonymous_enable=YES
write_enable=NO
anon_root=/home/ftp
}}

==== Anonymous read/write access ====

{{Warning|Allowing anonymous public read/write access is considered a ''very'' high security risk.}}

{{RootCmd|chown ftp /home/ftp}}

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/vsftpd/vsftpd.conf|1=
listen=YES
local_enable=NO
anonymous_enable=YES
anon_upload_enable=YES
write_enable=YES
anon_mkdir_write_enable=YES
anon_root=/home/ftp
}}

== Service ==

=== OpenRC ===

{{RootCmd
|rc-update add vsftpd default
|/etc/init.d/vsftpd start
}}

=== systemd ===

{{RootCmd
|systemctl enable vsftpd
|systemctl start vsftpd
}}

== Troubleshooting ==

=== seccomp filter sanboxing with vsftpd 3.0.x ===

The following error may occur on ftp clients with vsftpd 3.0.x:

<pre>500 OOPS: priv_sock_get_cmd</pre>

This is caused by [[Wikipedia:Seccomp|seccomp filter sanboxing]], which is enabled by default on {{Keyword|amd64}}. To workaround this issue, disable seccomp filter sanboxing:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/vsftpd/vsftpd.conf|1=
seccomp_sandbox=NO
}}

For further information, refer to Red Hat [https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=845980 bug #845980].

